            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I would suggest flipping Phase 1 and Phase 2: Start with non-public infrastructure that is used under the hood (just like the existing archive plugins, which also don't expose any interface), then take stock on how (and whether!) this could usefully be exposed -- this should be driven by actual plugin -- and existing API -- demand, not proactive exposure.\n\nBut +1 on decoupling this and turning this into composable, single-concern, functions (whether public or not).",
